[2] Sri Lanka
Date: Thu 24 Jun 2010
Source: Colombo Page [edited]
<http://www.colombopage.com/archive_10A/Jun24_1277393295KA.php>


The latest statistics on dengue from the Epidemiology Unit of the
Health Ministry says 113 dengue victims have died so far this year
[2010]. The number of dengue patients so far diagnosed increased to 17
411, although it has been declining from a high of 4672 in January to
a low of 1888 in May 2010, the statistics showed.

The month of June 2010 has shown a rise in the number of cases to 1943
[this number conflicts with those in the next sentence. - Mod.JW] due
to the devastating floods last month [May 2010] in most parts of the
country. The highest number of patients, 2354, was diagnosed from
Colombo, the most developed district of the country. Jaffna and
Gampaha districts also showed high prevalence of the disease. The
number of patients diagnosed in Jaffna district is 2181, while 2129
were found from Gampaha district. There were 1253 patients traced from
Ratnapura district, while 1048 cases have been reported from
Batticaloa district. The outbreak of dengue was remarkable in
Kurunegala, Puttalam, Ampara and Kalutara districts as well, points
out the Epidemiology Unit of the Ministry of Health.

The Epidemiology Unit urges the public to keep their environments
clean to prevent breeding of the dengue mosquitoes.

