[The 19 Jun 2010 edition of Tempo
(<http://www.prensa-latina.cu/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=199023&Itemid=1>) indicated that they were 10-15 patients daily being admitted to the Seguro Social Hospital in Tegucigalpa. The country has had 10 780 dengue cases so far in 2010; 461 of these are cases of hemorrhagic dengue fever, with people under 19 years of age as the main victims, and 10
deaths.

